# Environment variables for game-writing.com
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values you need:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` is gitignored (never commit real secrets). Every variable below is
# OPTIONAL and degrades gracefully when unset, so the site builds fine with an
# empty `.env`. For preview/production these are set as Vercel Environment
# Variables instead. Variables are declared with a typed schema in
# `astro.config.ts`; see the "Environment Variables" section of README.md.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE_CALENDAR_API_KEY  (secret / server, optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server-side Google Calendar API key. Read at build time in
# `src/pages/events.astro` to fetch upcoming events via `googleapis`. When
# unset, /events shows a "not configured" message instead of failing the build.
#
# Get one from: https://console.cloud.google.com/ -> APIs & Services -> Credentials
# Enable "Google Calendar API" first, then create an API key.
GOOGLE_CALENDAR_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION  (public / client, optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Search Console verification token, emitted as a <meta> tag in
# `src/layouts/Layout.astro` only when set. Normally left unset: the domain is
# already verified via a DNS TXT record, making this meta-tag method redundant.
# Uncomment and set only if you need the meta-tag verification method.
# PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=
